<denchmark-h:h1>Bug Report</denchmark-h>
 
 <denchmark-h:h3>Describe the bug</denchmark-h>
 
 collect_snippets writes warning messages to console.
 <denchmark-h:h3>System information</denchmark-h>
 
 
 OS Platform and Distribution:  macOS Catalina
 Python version: 3.7
 
 <denchmark-h:h3>Reproduction instructions</denchmark-h>
 
 <denchmark-code>git clone --quiet https://github.com/onnx/onnx.git
 pushd onnx
 git submodule update --quiet --init --recursive
 python -m venv ../env
 source ../env/bin/activate
 python -m pip install --quiet --upgrade pip
 python -m pip install --quiet protobuf
 export ONNX_ML=1
 export ONNX_NAMESPACE=onnx
 python -m pip install --quiet .
 popd
 python -c "from onnx.backend.test.case import collect_snippets; snippets = collect_snippets()"
 deactivate
 </denchmark-code>
 
 <denchmark-h:h3>Expected behavior</denchmark-h>
 
 No text is printed to console.
 <denchmark-h:h3>Actual behavior</denchmark-h>
 
 <denchmark-code>~/env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/onnx/backend/test/case/node/reduce_log_sum_exp.py:32: RuntimeWarning: overflow encountered in log
   np.exp(data), axis=tuple(axes), keepdims=keepdims == 1))
 ~/env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/onnx/backend/test/case/node/reduce_log_sum_exp.py:67: RuntimeWarning: overflow encountered in log
   keepdims=keepdims == 1))
 ~/env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/onnx/backend/test/case/node/reduce_log_sum_exp.py:103: RuntimeWarning: overflow encountered in log
   keepdims=keepdims == 1))
 ~/env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/onnx/backend/test/case/node/reduce_log_sum_exp.py:136: RuntimeWarning: overflow encountered in log
   keepdims=keepdims == 1))
 </denchmark-code>
 
 <denchmark-link:https://github.com/neginraoof>@neginraoof</denchmark-link>

 I encountered the same error only on MacOS (Windows works fine) when using some commands.
 Using longer float type should fix this warning. I will propose a PR <denchmark-link:https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/2878>#2878</denchmark-link>
  and cc <denchmark-link:https://github.com/neginraoof>@neginraoof</denchmark-link>
  for review.
 Thank you for reporting this bug!
